<subSubSection id="C3046513FFCAFFCAFEEAA20B2B42AEAC" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA13698FFCAFFC9FEEAA20B2DF1A81B" blockId="13.[264,1323,1839,1905]" box="[264,934,1839,1865]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Coloration and structure similar to that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFCAFFC9FD16A20B2DC8A81A" box="[756,927,1839,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrostriata">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFCAFFC9FD16A20B2DC8A81A" box="[756,927,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">V. rubrostriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA13698FFCAFFCAFEDAA2732DFFAED4" blockId="13.[264,1323,1839,1905]" lastBlockId="14.[264,1324,284,950]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFCAFFC9FEDAA2732FB4A822" box="[312,483,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygophore similar to that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFCAFFC9FCA0A2732DBAA822" box="[834,1005,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrostriata">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFCAFFC9FCA0A2732DBAA822" box="[834,1005,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">V. rubrostriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but ventral processes slen­ der, throughout their length, acutely pointed distally. Denticles on segment X very small. Aedeagal shaft longer than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFC9FFCAFD9AA4602D65AE0F" box="[632,818,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubsrostriata">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFC9FFCAFD9AA4602D65AE0F" box="[632,818,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">V. rubsrostriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with slender, ventro­apical process. Style with basally stout apophysis, narrowing to an acute apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA13698FFC9FFCAFEDAA4B02B42AEAC" blockId="14.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFC9FFCAFEDAA4B02FB5AEFF" box="[312,482,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Measurements</emphasis>
: Male 
<number id="3DD624BFFFC9FFCAFDD4A4B02C0CAEFC" box="[566,603,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.8">5.8</number>
(
<number id="3DD624BFFFC9FFCAFD89A4B02C92AEFC" box="[619,709,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.9" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.6">5.6–6.2</number>
) mm long, 
<number id="3DD624BFFFC9FFCAFCADA4B02D24AEFC" box="[847,883,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.3">1.3</number>
(
<number id="3DD624BFFFC9FFCAFC66A4B02D89AEFC" box="[900,990,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.3</number>
) mm wide across hind margin of head, 
<number id="3DD624BFFFC9FFCAFE78A4982FE9AE84" box="[410,446,444,470]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.4">1.4</number>
(
<number id="3DD624BFFFC9FFCAFE2CA4982C7FAE84" box="[462,552,444,470]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.5</number>
) mm wide across hind margin of pronotum. Female 
<quantity id="4CE69B7DFFC9FFCAFB6DA4982ABFAE84" box="[1167,1256,444,470]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="6.8">6.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CE69B7DFFC9FFCAFEEAA4C02F35AEAC" box="[264,354,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
wide across hind margin of head, 
<quantity id="4CE69B7DFFC9FFCAFD17A4C02D19AEAC" box="[757,846,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
wide across hind margin of pronotum.
</paragraph>
